## Build Limits (from shared constants)

| Metric | Limit | Constant |
|--------|-------|----------|
| Max build time | 15 minutes | `BUILD_LIMITS.MAX_BUILD_TIME_MS` |
| Max image size | 2 GB | `BUILD_LIMITS.MAX_IMAGE_SIZE_BYTES` |
| Concurrent builds | 1 (sequential) | `BUILD_LIMITS.CONCURRENT_BUILDS` |
| Build cache per project | 1 GB | `BUILD_LIMITS.BUILD_CACHE_SIZE_BYTES` |
| Images retained per project | 10 | `BUILD_LIMITS.MAX_IMAGES_PER_PROJECT` |

---

## Security Considerations

1. **Secret scrubbing in build logs**: Before storing or streaming logs, scan for patterns matching API keys, tokens, passwords, `DATABASE_URL` connection strings, and any value from the project's `env_vars` table marked `is_secret`. Replace with `***REDACTED***`.
2. **Installation token in clone URL**: The git clone uses `https://x-access-token:{token}@github.com/{owner}/{repo}.git`. The token must not appear in logs. Scrub the full URL and replace with `https://github.com/{owner}/{repo}.git`.
3. **Temporary build directories**: Clone and build artifacts are written to `BUILD_DIR`. Always clean up after build (success or failure) using try/finally.
4. **Docker socket access**: The platform process needs access to `/var/run/docker.sock`. This is a privileged operation -- the platform container runs with the Docker socket mounted.
5. **Build timeout enforcement**: A 15-minute hard timeout kills the build process and any child processes (git, npm, docker build) to prevent resource exhaustion.
